@node Storyline_Steven_Spielberg_Would_Be_Proud_Of

3 minutes into the future...Noel is the proud owner of the mighty Noel P. Davies Esq. EVIL company:-
A pleasure to take money away from you. He use underhand dealings to earn more power and more money.
And the hero of this game happens to work for them. I never said you were working for good guys...

Matthew arrives by foot to the towering skyscraper that can be seen for miles (oddly, no matter which
way you're facing you can still see it). Matthew pushes the revolving door too hard and spins around
in it accidentally, trapping several obese people. Never mind. Undaunted, Matthew carries on. To his
dismay the coffee machine still refuses to work. "I NEED CAFFEINE!" Matthew screams. Calming himself
down (actually, someone just knocked him out with a handbag), Matthew walks casually to the lift. Too
casually in fact, as he knocks over a pot plant and hilariously falls over. Now with his newly soiled
trousers (for want of a better word) he glides to the lift only to find the lift is naturally out of
order (you're not bored yet are you?).

16 minutes later

After running up 37 flights of stairs, Matthew eventually (thank God) reaches the door of the head of
the company, Noel P. Davies Esq. (the "e" is silent).

"Come in."

Matthew opens the door and strides up to the silhouetted figure.

"I trust your last mission went well, fighting the poisoned monkeys in Rangoon and Zanzibar."
Noel suavely purrs in a very English accent (not that this is his real voice, natch).

"Yes. Yes it did."

"Good. I have 3 more missions for you. You will get paid £7.99 for completing all of them."

"Woohoo!"

"You are to go to Skegness and destroy the malfunctioned toy factory."

"OK."

So Matthew catches the next taxi to Skegness. Here we go.

@endnode

@node Can_I?

This marvellous 10 level demo requires an A1200 to really function properly. An accelerated Amiga
would be a superb idea, though not too accelerated. Don't expect it, for example, to work on a 20Ghz PPC
 (would be nice, wouldn't it?) with WarpUp or something like that.
 I have not tested this game on anything other than an A1200 '030/50 MHz. It works fine on this. 
 Play the demo and judge for yourself how quick it is. If it's too fast, try disabling the CPU caches or something.
 You will also require a joypad, and a massive 1.5 MB to install onto the hard drive. 
Provided you haven't eaten up the rest of your hard drive by installing Genetic Species or something.

@endnode

@node Instructions

Standard controls apply. Experiment with the three guns that are available. Only one can be fired in
mid-air.

Special things:-

1. Indestructaball- these cannot be destroyed. Simply avoid.

2. The mysterious duck- When you touch these, odd things can occur. A block may suddenly disappear
nearby or you can be teleported. Sometimes you need to press "Space" to enable the effect.

3. The red eeeeeevil face- these don't appear to do any harm. Try destroying them to see what
happens.

4. Spikes- all hurt, some more than others.

5. Flaming pit- This does not really help you on your quest. Kills you quicker than you can say
"Ginger Flavoured Crisps".

@endnode

